# Fluff Date: 2026-02-28 17:47:08
<overview>
<p>The Crucible Station is the most secure intelligence and detention facility operated by the Maskirovka, the Capellan Confederation's feared internal and external intelligence service. Commissioned in 3065 and placed in isolated orbit around Nuwa, one of Sian's moons, this 6,000-ton space station was designed from the outset to exploit the vacuum of space as its primary perimeter. The facility serves as the Maskirovka's most modern interrogation center, housing individuals deemed too sensitive or too dangerous for any conventional planetary prison. Its existence is suspected by rival intelligence agencies throughout the Inner Sphere, but its precise location is not publicly documented, and the Confederation has never officially acknowledged the station's presence. No prisoner assigned to Crucible Station has ever been confirmed to have departed the facility.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>The Crucible Station is a 6,000-ton platform measuring 400 meters in length and 450 meters in width, built for sustained independent operation with minimal resupply requirements. One hundred fifty double heat sinks manage thermal output across the station's systems and habitable areas. Two 450-meter diameter gravity decks provide acceptable living conditions for the crew and occupants during extended deployments.</p><p>Defensively, each of the station's four weapon arcs mounts a battery of three ER Large Lasers capable of engaging targets at long range, three Small Pulse Lasers providing close-in point defense, and two SRM-6 launchers for short-range engagements. The armament is designed to deter small infiltration craft and lightly armed rescue vessels, the threat profile considered most credible by the station's designers. Against any serious military force, the station's defenses are insufficient, and the design relies on concealment and proximity to a covert interceptor squadron based on Nuwa's surface for its primary tactical protection.</p><p>Six small craft berths support intra-system logistics, though no craft are permanently assigned to reduce the station's observable traffic signature. Nine foot infantry platoon berths accommodate the CCAF security battalion responsible for prisoner control and internal security. Cargo capacity stands at approximately 554 tons, supplemented by a dedicated 500-ton fuel bunker that extends the intervals between resupply runs and further limits the frequency of traffic that might reveal the station's location. With no DropShip docking capacity and no permanently assigned small craft, Crucible is effectively self-contained during standard operational periods.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>The Crucible Station occupies an isolated orbit around Nuwa, one of Sian's moons in the Capellan Confederation's capital system. Access is controlled entirely by the Maskirovka, with logistics conducted through intra-system craft launched from moon-based facilities. Mowang couriers and ST-46-style shuttles serve as the primary resupply vehicles, with no permanent small craft berthed aboard the station. The station's orbital parameters are not publicized, and its air defense relies on a dedicated squadron of interceptors maintained on Nuwa's surface rather than aboard the station itself. Sian's status as the Capellan capital means any infiltrating vessel faces multiple layers of system defense before approaching the moon, making rescue or assault operations extraordinarily difficult to execute. The station serves a single operator, the Maskirovka, and carries no commercial or civilian function.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The Maskirovka earned its reputation as the Inner Sphere's most methodical intelligence service through decades of operations that left rival agencies consistently uncertain of its methods, reach, and facilities. That reputation drew sustained attention, and by the late thirty-first century, Davion agents, St. Ives operatives, and Liao dissident networks had mounted repeated efforts to locate and raid or destroy Maskirovka interrogation centers. Ground-based facilities, however carefully concealed, remained vulnerable to compromise through escaped prisoners, civilian witnesses, and orbital reconnaissance conducted by enemy intelligence assets.</p><p>In 3060, the Maskirovka's leadership concluded that the fundamental problem was the planetary environment itself, and chose the vacuum of space as the answer. A purpose-built orbital station would have no civilian population to serve as witnesses, no accessible surface perimeter, and no practical approach route that could be used without passing through multiple layers of Sian's system defenses. Construction was conducted under strict internal security protocols, and the resulting facility was activated in 3065 in an isolated orbit around Nuwa. The choice of lunar orbit placed the station within reach of a dedicated interceptor force based on Nuwa's surface, providing an armed response to any approaching vessel without broadcasting the station's location through visible traffic patterns.</p><p>Within eighteen months of activation, Crucible had already become home to some of the most sensitive prisoners in the Confederation, including individuals drawn from the St. Ives and Liao dissident communities and other political detainees the Maskirovka considered too dangerous for any conventional facility. The station's normal contingent consists of a dozen senior analysts and forty interrogators, supported by a full CCAF marine battalion responsible for the movement and containment of up to 300 prisoners simultaneously. Each prisoner is held in an individual cell with integrated interrogation facilities, making it unnecessary to move detainees to separate rooms. The design eliminates the movement corridors and transfer moments that have historically been exploited in prisoner recovery operations. The six grave decks, each 185 meters in diameter, house all interrogation rooms, administrative areas, and prisoner cells in a self-contained internal structure.</p><p>Enemy intelligence services have confirmed the station's existence, and considerable resources have been devoted to pinpointing its location. Sian is rarely attacked directly given its status as the Capellan capital, and any infiltration vessel attempting to reach Nuwa's orbital vicinity faces both the system's conventional defenses and the specific interceptor coverage maintained around the moon. No successful operation against the station has been documented, and no prisoner assigned to Crucible has been confirmed to have left it.</p>
</history>

